  "original_title": "Resolving economic crisis : President stresses special focus on agriculture",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Resolving economic crisis : President stresses special focus on agriculture",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "More focus should be made on agriculture when it comes to resolving the current economic crisis, President Ranil Wickremesinghe said.",
        "Wickremesinghe made this remark when he met the Chief Incumbent of Atamasthana and Chief Sanganayaka of North Central region of Somapali Maha Nikaya affiliated to Malwathu Maha Vihamra Venerable Pallegama Siriniwasa Thera in Anurdhapura on Saturday according to the President\u2019s office.",
        "The President assured that the government will provide fertilizer needed for the Maha Season.",
        "\u201cWe have already begun providing fertilizer for Coconut, Tea and Rubber plantations while focus is also made on promoting the cultivation of maize. Maize is essential as chicken feed and we hope to revive the poultry industry which has come to a standstill as a result of non availability of animal feed,\u201d the President said.",
        "He said the task of resolving issues in Anurdhapura District will be assigned to MPs in the district.",
        "Also, the President informed the Thera that the government intends to promote historical Maha Vihara where excavations are done at the moment as a tourist attraction. (Yohan Perera)"
      ],
